title: Drawing, Design for Six-legged Sideboard with Rounded Front and Four Drawers, 1900–05
title_raw: Design for Six-legged Sideboard with Rounded Front and Four Drawers
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite above design: 6.0" long; at right of design with arrows pointing to decorative medallion and a drawer front: inlay; below drawer: #3
creditline: Gift of The Lake St. Louis Historical Society
description: Sideboard on six straight tapered legs; rounded front edges each with medallion motif; four rectangular drawings in central section with C-shaped handles and keyholes; low backsplash at back of top.

participants.person_name: The Lake St. Louis Historical Society

tombstone.epitaph:
Drawing, Design for Six-legged Sideboard with Rounded Front and Four Drawers, 1900–05. Graphite on thin cream paper. 
Gift of The Lake St. Louis Historical Society. 2000-69-7
